假设已知电机在不同转速下的扭矩和功率数据，我们可以将它们存储在两个数组中，然后在 MATLAB 中进行插值和计算。以下是一个简单的 MATLAB 代码示例：

```matlab
% 电机转速[rpm]、扭矩[Nm]和功率[kW]数据
rpm = [0, 1000, 2000, 3000, 4000, 5000, 6000, 7000, 8000];
torque = [300, 290, 280, 270, 250, 220, 190, 150, 100];
power = [0, 29.84, 57.73, 84.36, 107.0, 121.48, 126.60, 114.56, 87.96];

% 转换转速单位到rad/s，功率单位到W
rpm_rad = rpm * (2*pi/60);
power_watt = power * 1000;

% 根据已知的电机输出扭矩和功率数据，在给定的转速范围内进行插值
rpm_interp = linspace(min(rpm), max(rpm), 1000);
torque_interp = interp1(rpm, torque, rpm_interp, 'spline');
power_interp = interp1(rpm, power_watt, rpm_interp, 'spline');

% 计算车辆加速度，速度和行驶距离（假设一些车辆参数）
m = 1500;  % 车辆质量 [kg]
r = 0.3;   % 轮胎半径 [m]
eta = 0.9; % 传动效率
g = 9.81;  % 重力加速度 [m/s^2]
Cr = 0.015;% 轮胎滚动阻力系数
Cd = 0.34; % 空气阻力系数
A = 2.2;   % 车辆前进面积 [m^2]
rho = 1.225;% 空气密度 [kg/m^3]
t = 0:0.1:100; % 时间序列 [s]

% 初始化加速度、速度和行驶距离数据
a = zeros(1, length(t));
v = zeros(1, length(t));
s = zeros(1, length(t));

for i = 1:length(t)
    % 计算车辆加速度
    a(i) = (power_interp(i)/v(i) * eta * r / m) - g * Cr - 0.5 * rho * Cd * A * v(i)^2 / m;
    % 计算车辆速度和行驶距离
    if i > 1
        v(i) = v(i-1) + a(i) * 0.1;
        s(i) = s(i-1) + v(i) * 0.1 + 0.5 * a(i) * 0.1^2;
    end
end

% 绘制图形
figure;
subplot(2,2,1);
plot(rpm_interp, torque_interp);
xlabel('转速 [rpm]');
ylabel('扭矩 [Nm]');
title('电机扭矩曲线');
grid on;

subplot(2,2,2);
plot(rpm_interp, power_interp);
xlabel('转速 [rpm]');
ylabel('功率 [W]');
title('电机功率曲线');
grid on;

subplot(2,2,3);
plot(t, a);
xlabel('时间 [s]');
ylabel('加速度 [m/s^2]');
title('车辆加速度');
grid on;

subplot(2,2,4);
plot(t, v);
xlabel('时间 [s]');
ylabel('速度 [m/s]');
title('车辆速度');
grid on;
```

Here's an example Java code for a table component that adapts dynamically to a given HashMap:

```java
import javax.swing.*;
import javax.swing.table.DefaultTableModel;
import java.awt.*;
import java.util.HashMap;
import java.util.Random;

public class HashMapTable extends JFrame {

    private final HashMap<String, Integer> map;

    public HashMapTable(HashMap<String, Integer> map) {
        super("HashMap Table");

        this.map = map;

        JTable table = new JTable(createTableModel(map));
        table.setAutoResizeMode(JTable.AUTO_RESIZE_ALL_COLUMNS);
        JScrollPane scrollPane = new JScrollPane(table);

        getContentPane().add(scrollPane);

        setSize(400, 300);
        setLocationRelativeTo(null);
        setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.EXIT_ON_CLOSE);
    }

    private DefaultTableModel createTableModel(HashMap<String, Integer> map) {
        int size = map.size();
        Object[][] data = new Object[size][2];
        String[] columns = {"Key", "Value"};

        // Randomize the order of keys and values
        String[] keys = map.keySet().toArray(new String[0]);
        shuffleArray(keys);

        Integer[] values = new Integer[size];
        for (int i = 0; i < size; i++) {
            values[i] = map.get(keys[i]);
        }
        shuffleArray(values);

        // Populate the data array with randomized keys and values
        for (int i = 0; i < size; i++) {
            data[i][0] = keys[i];
            data[i][1] = values[i];
        }

        return new DefaultTableModel(data, columns);
    }

    // Utility method to shuffle an array randomly
    private static void shuffleArray(Object[] array) {
        Random rnd = new Random();
        for (int i = array.length - 1; i > 0; i--) {
            int index = rnd.nextInt(i + 1);
            Object temp = array[index];
            array[index] = array[i];
            array[i] = temp;
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        HashMap<String, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        map.put("apple", 5);
        map.put("orange", 3);
        map.put("banana", 2);
        map.put("grapefruit", 4);
        map.put("pineapple", 1);

        HashMapTable tableFrame = new HashMapTable(map);
        tableFrame.setVisible(true);
    }
}
```

This code creates a JFrame with a JTable that displays the given HashMap. The keys and values of the HashMap are randomized, and the table adapts dynamically according to the size of the HashMap. The columns of the table are "Key" and "Value". The code also includes a utility method to shuffle an array randomly, which is used to randomize the order of keys and values. The main method creates an example HashMap and displays it in the table.

Here's the Java code to generate a random pronounceable word between 3 and 10 characters, then perform a Bing search with it and load the first result HTML URL content to a String value.

```java
import java.io.BufferedReader;
import java.io.InputStreamReader;
import java.net.HttpURLConnection;
import java.net.URL;
import java.util.Random;

public class BingSearch {

    private static final String BING_SEARCH_URL = "https://www.bing.com/search?q=";
    private static final String USER_AGENT = "Mozilla/5.0";

    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
        String randomWord = getRandomPronounceableWord(3, 10);
        System.out.println("Random word: " + randomWord);

        String searchUrl = BING_SEARCH_URL + randomWord;
        String htmlContent = getHtmlContentFromUrl(searchUrl);

        System.out.println("First search result HTML content: " + htmlContent);
    }

    private static String getRandomPronounceableWord(int minLength, int maxLength) {
        String[] consonants = {"b", "c", "d", "f", "g", "h", "j", "k", "l", "m", "n", "p", "qu", "r", "s", "t", "v", "w", "x", "y", "z"};
        String[] vowels = {"a", "e", "i", "o", "u"};

        Random rnd = new Random();
        int length = minLength + rnd.nextInt(maxLength - minLength + 1);
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();

        for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
            if (i % 2 == 0) {
                sb.append(consonants[rnd.nextInt(consonants.length)]);
            } else {
                sb.append(vowels[rnd.nextInt(vowels.length)]);
            }
        }

        return sb.toString();
    }

    private static String getHtmlContentFromUrl(String url) throws Exception {
        URL obj = new URL(url);
        HttpURLConnection con = (HttpURLConnection) obj.openConnection();

        con.setRequestMethod("GET");
        con.setRequestProperty("User-Agent", USER_AGENT);

        int responseCode = con.getResponseCode();
